The paper deals with frames, which are a signal processing tool, and specifically with discrete Fourier transform (DFT) codes. The paper also discusses a new application of frames, namely, distributed source coding that uses DFT codes for compression. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the study of communication systems and their properties. 

The paper also discusses the extreme eigenvalues of DFT frames and their subframes, which is related to spectral analysis and signal processing. Therefore, it could also belong to cs.SI (Signal Processing), cs.SP (Speech Processing), or cs.MM (Multimedia). 

Finally, the paper discusses the best and worst systematic frames in the minimum mean-squared reconstruction error sense, which is related to machine learning and optimization. Therefore, it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
